com.googlecode.cqengine.metadata

Class AttributeMetadata<A,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.metadata.AttributeMetadata<A,O>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SortedAttributeMetadata

    public class AttributeMetadata<A,O>
extends Object
    Provides access to basic metadata for a given attribute, in unsorted order.

    This requires in advance, an index which implements the KeyStatisticsAttributeIndex interface, to be added to the collection on the given attribute. See MetadataEngine for more details.

    This object can be accessed first by calling IndexedCollection.getMetadataEngine() to access the MetadataEngine, and then by calling MetadataEngine.getAttributeMetadata(Attribute) for a given attribute.

    • Method Detail

      • getFrequencyDistribution

        public Stream<KeyFrequency<A>> getFrequencyDistribution()
        Returns the frequencies of distinct keys (a.k.a. attribute values) in the index.

        The KeyFrequency objects encapsulate a key (a.k.a. attribute value), and the frequency (or count) of how many objects in the collection match that key.

      • getKeysAndValues

        public Stream<KeyValue<A,O>> getKeysAndValues()
        Returns the keys (a.k.a. attribute values) and the objects they match in the index.

        Note the same key will be returned multiple times if more than one object has the same key. Also the same object might be returned multiple times, each time for a different key, if the index is built on a multi-value attribute.

        Returns:
        The keys and objects they match in the index
